JIRA_BASE_URL=https://yourcompany.atlassian.net
JIRA_EMAIL=your@email.com
JIRA_API_TOKEN=your_jira_api_token
JIRA_PROJECT_KEY=YOUR_PROJECT_KEY
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_key
ADMIN_USERNAME=admin
ADMIN_PASSWORD=yourpassword
PORT=3000
```

**Step 4 — Go to Source Control in VS Code**

Click the **branch icon** in the left sidebar (or press `Ctrl + Shift + G`)

**Step 5 — Initialise the repo**

Click **"Initialize Repository"** button

**Step 6 — Stage all files**

Click the **+** icon next to "Changes" to stage all files. You should see all your files appear under "Staged Changes". Make sure `.env` is NOT in the list — if it is, your `.gitignore` isn't saved yet.

**Step 7 — Commit**

Type a message in the box at the top:
```
initial commit - Jira AI agent with JWT auth and web UI